Female (
paratype
) ( Fig. 44 ): Pedipalps slightly shorter than on male ( Fig. 52 ), 1.6 times longer than propeltidium length. Setation as on male except for anterior sternum with 10 setae. Flagellum with three flagellomeres ( Figs. 48–50 ). Setation: seta Dl2 reduced and anterior to Vl1 ; Dl3 posterior to Vl2 ; Vm2 present and not reduced; seta Vm1 at same level as Vm2 ; microsetae Dl1 and Dl4 present. Spermathecae ( Fig. 56 ) with two pairs of lobes, with bases fused and at the same level; median pair inverse “J” shaped outwards, longer than lateral pair, with duct openings along the entire length, ending in a blunt tip; lateral pair slender and shorter, about 1/2 length of median lobes, without duct openings, ending in a blunt tip. Chitinized arch U- shaped; with a wide lateral tip and without anterior branch. Gonopod 3.6 times wider than long, sub rectangular-shaped. Chelicera: serrula with 13 teeth. Setal group formula 3-6-4-2-7-6-1-5. Fixed finger with four teeth between two primary teeth.
